data_structure.leagues: Array of league identifiers (nfl, nba, mlb, etc.)
data_structure.odds: Market odds data for specific league and bet type

sample_types: Both Teams to Score 1+ Passing TD
Both Players to Win a Set
Team to Score 1+ Rush TD Every Game
Team to Advance to X Round
Player Not to Lose a Service Game

BoltOdds.url_structure: Simple REST API with sport/sportsbook filtering
BoltOdds.data_format: JSON arrays with nested market data
BoltOdds.filtering: By sport name and/or sportsbook name

TheOddsAPI.url_structure: RESTful API with sport keys and regions
TheOddsAPI.filtering: By sport key, region, and market type

Unabated.url_structure: API with numeric league/bet type IDs
Unabated.data_format: JSON data organized by league and bet type
Unabated.filtering: By league identifier and numeric bet type ID

authentication.TheOddsAPI: API key required (free tier with limits)

strengths: Standardized sport keys and market types
Multiple data types (odds, people, sources, teams)
weaknesses: Requires knowledge of numeric bet type IDs

examples.description: Get all available sports and sportsbooks
Get all games for a specific sport
Get games for specific sport and sportsbook

examples.sample_response: Array of games with bookmaker odds
Array of completed games with scores
Object with bet type IDs and names

integration_strategy.multi_provider_approach: Use all three for maximum coverage and data redundancy
integration_strategy.primary_secondary_setup: TheOddsAPI as primary (broad coverage), BoltOdds as secondary (sportsbook diversity)
integration_strategy.specialized_use: Unabated for professional trading and analytics
integration_strategy.cost_optimization: Start with free tiers, upgrade based on usage needs

technical_considerations.rate_limiting: All providers have rate limits, implement proper throttling
technical_considerations.data_normalization: Different data structures require normalization layer
technical_considerations.error_handling: Implement robust error handling for API failures
technical_considerations.caching_strategy: Cache responses appropriately to minimize API calls
technical_considerations.monitoring: Monitor API usage and costs across all providers
